	 Gynecologist is&nbsp;a&nbsp;doctor specializing on&nbsp;treatment of&nbsp;women’s diseases, especially those of&nbsp;the reproductive organs. Feeling well and not having any complaints should not prevent you from visiting a&nbsp;doctor. A&nbsp;planned check-up once a&nbsp;year is&nbsp;necessary as&nbsp;it&nbsp;can help to&nbsp;diagnose a&nbsp;number of&nbsp;diseases at&nbsp;early stages.
</p>
<p>
	 In&nbsp;ICRM, you can see highly qualified doctors, do&nbsp;all necessary tests and diagnostic procedures. You can choose a&nbsp;doctor using our website and make an&nbsp;appointment for a&nbsp;gynecology consultation either by&nbsp;making a&nbsp;call or&nbsp;with the help of&nbsp;the <a href="#contactus" data-modal-open="">contact form</a>.
</p>
<p>
	 During your initial consultation, the doctor will listen to&nbsp;your complaints and ask questions to&nbsp;complete your case history. The questions will be&nbsp;about your previous reproductive diseases, gynecologic surgeries, pregnancies and deliveries, about your sexual life and contraception methods you use. If&nbsp;you want to&nbsp;discuss something that worries you, please give our doctor a&nbsp;detailed description of&nbsp;the symptoms. You can bring any recent ultrasound and test results. The doctor will offer examination on&nbsp;the gynecological chair with the help of&nbsp;a&nbsp;speculum, perform bimanual exam (palpation) of&nbsp;the uterus, ovaries and the fallopian tubes. If&nbsp;necessary, our doctor will refer you to&nbsp;colposcopy, ultrasound or&nbsp;other examinations.
</p>
<p>
	 When to&nbsp;consult a&nbsp;gynecologist?
</p>
<p>
	 You should visit a&nbsp;gynecologist for annual check-ups, when you plan a&nbsp;family, or&nbsp;if&nbsp;you have the following symptoms:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Late period.</li>
	<li>Heavy, prolonged, painful bleedings.</li>
	<li>Irregular periods.</li>
	<li>Lower abdominal pain.</li>
	<li>Unusual changes in&nbsp;vaginal discharge.</li>
	<li>Vulva itching and/or burning.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 The earlier you come to&nbsp;see a&nbsp;doctor, the faster the diagnosis will be&nbsp;made and your treatment will be&nbsp;started. You can prevent development of&nbsp;the disease into its chronic stage and avoid complications.
</p>
<p>
	 Please, use our <a href="#contactus" data-modal-open="">contact form</a> to&nbsp;make an&nbsp;appointment. Our International Manager will contact you to&nbsp;offer convenient date and time. You can also make an&nbsp;appointment for the online consultation. However, please, remember that an&nbsp;online consultation cannot be&nbsp;equal to&nbsp;actually seeing a&nbsp;doctor.
